<item>
            <title>[LU-18030] ll_set_acl eats permissions if they could be expressed with mode bits</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18030</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ll_set_acl() has this code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;switch (type) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; case ACL_TYPE_ACCESS:
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; name = XATTR_NAME_POSIX_ACL_ACCESS;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if (acl)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; rc = posix_acl_update_mode(map, inode,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;&amp;amp;inode-&amp;gt;i_mode, &amp;amp;acl);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; break;

...
       }
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;if (acl) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; value_size = posix_acl_xattr_size(acl-&amp;gt;a_count);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; value = kmalloc(value_size, GFP_NOFS);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if (value == NULL)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; GOTO(out, rc = -ENOMEM);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; rc = posix_acl_to_xattr(&amp;amp;init_user_ns, acl, value, value_size);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if (rc &amp;lt; 0)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; GOTO(out_value, rc);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; rc = md_setxattr(sbi-&amp;gt;ll_md_exp, ll_inode2fid(inode),
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;value ? OBD_MD_FLXATTR : OBD_MD_FLXATTRRM,
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;name, value, value_size, 0, 0, &amp;amp;req);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But posix_acl_update_mode() is setting the acl argument to NULL if the passed in ACL is expressible as just mode bits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This code path apparently is only used via NFS server reexport path, direct setfacl calls go straght into setxattr.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So we either need to catch this and do setattr_md call to transfer the updated mode information, or I guess we invalidate the permission bits anyway on setattr so might as well skip the posix_acl_update_mode() call altogether and let the server tell us the new permissions next time we refresh?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
